http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/blfs/view/cvs/server/bind.html BIND was originally created by the students of California University at Barkeley in the early 1980s

it stands for Berkeley Internet Name Domain (BIND),it's the reference implementation of the Domain Name System (DNS) protocols It is a popular software for translating domain names into IP addresses for Linux servers it is a transparent open source software BIND is a very flexible, full-featured DNS system

https://www.isc.org/downloads/bind/
